The Taurus PT1911 is a clone of the US Military model 1911 single-action recoil operated semi-automatic pistol. title: For Sale/Trade:  Sheridan Blue Streak   *** SOLD PENDING PAYMENT ***
postcontent: Vintage & gorgeous, outstanding quality 5MM SHERIDAN BLUE STREAK RIFLE, still in superb overall condition & quite functional, consisting of early, matched American Walnut "slim-line" forend & buttstock, plus blued steel trigger guard and adjustable rear sight on barrel, hooked front sight and early "push-down" safety located on the back end cap of the air tube with "Hold Down To Fire" imprinted in circle above. Solid, pear shaped bolt (not later hollow type) and fine line grooved receiver top. Strokes up correctly & holds. Very powerful and accurate. Blackened bronze pump tube & barrel still has about 90%+ original finish as well. Caliber is standard Sheridan 5mm (.20 Cal) and this vintage Blue Streak model is marked on right side of reciever with older, fine line inscription reading: "Sheridan Products Inc." ... "Racine, Wisconsin" ... "Made In U.S.A" of course, and probably dates from the late 1950s or early 1960s era. Condition is excellent still with NO cracks or dings and only some incidental wear. There were NO serial numbers on these early Sheridans, and the stock was built for adults (not youths) and this rifle measures about 37" OAL. Other than the Model A & B Super-grades which immediately preceded these early Streaks, Sheridan never produced a more svelte & powerful pneumatic arm.  Missing one of these early Blue Streaks of this early style & configuration from your private collection or display? Well look no further 'cause this vintage, high quality Sheridan Blue Streak is the real deal, still in superb overall condition, for the astute buyer or collector. They haven't made 'em like this gorgeous example in well over half a Century, and they do not come onto the market in this condition often ... so it's really a no-brainer.I've seen them sell (not just listed) for over $200 online.
